POLICE have arrested one suspect on Friday in connection with the Katlehong tavern shooting. The suspect is said to be an member of the Ekurhuleni Metro Police Department. (EMPD) The suspect is expected to appear before Palm Ridge Magistrates' Court on 25 July 2022. Police said the investigation continues regarding this matter. Police spokeswoman Colonel Dimakatso Sello said, “The public is still urged to report any criminal activities on the police crime stop hotline at 08600 10111 or anonymously via MySaps app. All information received will be treated as strictly confidential.” Three weeks ago on 08 July 2022, two people were shot and killed at a tavern in Katlehong. The incident also left at least four others injured. Sello had previously said in a media statement, “It is reported that four men, of which one of them was armed with a 9mm pistol entered the tavern and started shooting randomly at patrons. Six people were shot, leaving two dead on the scene and four injured.” READ: Two die in tavern shooting! Ekurhuleni MMC for Safety, Lethlogonolo Moseki has called for justice to be served following the arrest of a suspect allegedly involved in the Katlehong tavern shooting that took place on Friday, 8 July 2022. "The city can confirm that the arrested individual is an employee of the Ekurhuleni Metropolitan Police Department. Furthermore, disciplinary procedures are currently being instituted against the individual. “We applaud the police for the swift arrest of the suspected shooter in the Katlehong Tavern shooting. It doesn’t matter if he is a member of the EMPD, if the individual is guilty, justice must be served. The suspect will not receive any pity or special treatment from the side of the city. We will be observing the developments of this case with a close eye.” Said Moseki.  